    • isDistinct

      public boolean isDistinct()
      Description copied from interface: LabelIndex
      Returns whether or not the index is distinct.

      Index distinctness is based on whether the labels in the index can overlap or cannot overlap. In the case of distinct, non-overlapping labels optimization can be made to the process of searching for labels, as well as iteration over and size computation of sub-indices.

      Returns:
      Returns true if the index is distinct, false if the index is not distinct.
